President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Susan Burk as Special Representative of the President at the State Department, Raphael Bostic as Assistant Secretary for Policy Development and Research at the Department of Housing and Urban Development, Michelle J. DePass as Assistant Administrator for International Affairs at the Environmental Protection Agency, Cynthia J. Giles as Assistant Administrator for Enforcement and Compliance Assurance at the Environmental Protection Agency, Michael L. Connor as Director of the Bureau of Reclamation at the Department of the Interior, Scott Blake Harris as General Counsel at the Department of Energy, and Joseph C. Szabo as Administrator of the Federal Railroad Administration at the Department of Transportation. President Obama expressed confidence in their abilities to tackle the challenges ahead and praised their experience and expertise.